Long-time Hillsborough County political influencers Peggy Land and April Schiff will receive the Tampa Tiger Bay Clubâ€™s 2022 Lifetime Achievement Awards. The club annually honors one local Republican and one Democratic activist. Land, a Virginia native, grew up a Republican but has been a strong supporter of Democratic candidates for more than 20 years. She served on finance committees for presidential candidates Al Gore and John Kerry and attended their nominating conventions. Long active with the Salvation Army Tampa and Metropolitan Ministries, she is former Tiger Bay membership chairman. Schiff is a veteran local political consultant who worked on the campaigns of President George W. Bush, U.S. Sen. Mel Martinez, Governor Jeb Bush, and numerous legislators and local officeholders throughout Florida. She is currently the elected Hillsborough Republican state committeewoman and has been active in Tiger Bay and GOP and political consulting trade associations.